                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">733.35/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Uruguay (<persName type="to">Wright</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-17T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 17, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Your 41, July 16, midnight and your 42, July 17, 2 a.m. Department willing to
                    adopt any procedure that recommends itself to both Governments. The suggestion
                    for a personal conference of the Ministers of Foreign Affairs of both countries
                    under the auspices of the American diplomatic representatives on board the Coast
                    Guard vessels now in Montevideo would seem to be the most expeditious method,
                    provided these vessels are available for this purpose. The commander of these
                    ships should be consulted on this point.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
